Steps:
1. Open Server Manager on your Windows Server machine.
2. Click Tools > Group Policy Management to launch the Group Policy Management Console (GPMC).
3. In the left pane, expand your Forest > Domains > your domain name (e.g., "yourdomain.com").
4. Right-click Group Policy Objects and select New.
5. Name the new GPO No LLMNR, then click OK.
6. Right-click the newly created No LLMNR GPO and select Edit to open the Group Policy Management Editor.
7. In the left pane, navigate to:
Computer Configuration > Policies > Administrative Templates > Network > DNS Client
8. In the right pane, find and double-click Turn Off Multicast Name Resolution.
9. Select Enabled, then click Apply > OK.
10. Close the Group Policy Management Editor.
11. Back in Group Policy Management, right-click your GC Computers OU and select Link an Existing GPO.
12. Choose No LLMNR, then click OK.
